// ============================================================
// FLUX APPARITION — v8R3 "K3 Law Refinement"
// 
// WHAT CHANGED IN THIS PASS
// - Keeps the successful Tricera-style chorus from v8T2
// - Reverb only:
//   - lowers the reverb floor at minimum K3
//   - keeps mid K3 usable and plate-like
//   - trims the top end slightly so max is still rich but less excessive
//   - keeps the improved glue to dry signal
//   - adds decay-dependent diffusion: tighter at low K3, smoother at high K3
//   - SW4 is pushed a bit more toward character than pure size
//   - SW4 smoothing slowed further to reduce switching transient
// - Chorus unchanged
// - Freeze unchanged
// - Switching unchanged
//
// K1 Rate      Chorus LFO (0.1 - 3 Hz)
// K2 Mix       Dry/wet crossfade
// K3 Decay     Reverb feedback / tight->plate range (0.3 - 0.88)
// K4 Depth     Chorus modulation (0.2 - 5 ms)
// K5 Balance   Left=chorus  Center=both  Right=reverb
// K6 Tone      Resonant SVF on wet bus (300 - 5000 Hz)
//
// SW1 Shimmer   Octave-up pitch shift in reverb feedback
// SW2 Series    Off=parallel  On=series (order follows balance)
// SW3 Deep      Off=subtle ensemble  On=deeper / wider / hotter chorus
// SW4 Character Off=brighter/tighter plate  On=darker/wider hall
//
// FS1 Tap = chorus on/off
// FS2 Tap = reverb on/off   Hold(250ms) = freeze
//
// LED1: 0=off  1.0=chorus on
// LED2: 0=off  1.0=reverb on  0.65=frozen
// ============================================================

